2. Definitions

“Anthropic Entity” means:

(a) Anthropic, PBC;

(b) any entity directly or indirectly controlled by Anthropic, PBC; and

(c) any successor entity or entity that acquires all or substantially all of the business or assets of Anthropic, PBC.

“Excluded Party” means:

(a) an Anthropic Entity;

(b) Dario Amodei; or

(c) any person or entity acting on behalf of, at the direction of, or primarily for the benefit of an Anthropic Entity or Dario Amodei in connection with the Software.

A person is not an Excluded Party merely because that person:

(a) uses, subscribes to, purchases, or accesses a product or service provided by an Anthropic Entity;

(b) communicates with an Anthropic Entity;

(c) is a customer of an Anthropic Entity; or

(d) is employed or engaged by an Anthropic Entity but uses the Software solely in a personal capacity and not on behalf of or for the benefit of an Anthropic Entity.

Dario Amodei remains an Excluded Party whether acting personally or on behalf of another person or entity.

“Independent User” means any person or entity that is not an Excluded Party.

“Anthropic Service” means any artificial-intelligence model, agent, API, coding assistant, application, hosted service, computer-use system, or other automated tool provided or operated by an Anthropic Entity, including Claude, Claude Code, and the Anthropic API.

“Service Processing” means the reproduction, transmission, storage, caching, analysis, modification, execution, or other processing of the Software by an Anthropic Service when:

(a) the processing is initiated by an Independent User;

(b) the processing is performed solely to execute that Independent User’s instructions, provide functionality requested by that Independent User, or return results to that Independent User; and

(c) the processing is not performed on behalf of or primarily for the benefit of an Excluded Party.

“Software” means the software and associated documentation distributed with this License, including any substantial portion, modification, or derivative work containing code first published under this License.

