4. Exclusion of Anthropic and Dario Amodei

An Excluded Party may not, directly or indirectly:

(a) use, execute, access, copy, modify, merge, publish, distribute, sublicense, sell, host, deploy, study, evaluate, or create derivative works from the Software;

(b) use the Software to develop, train, evaluate, benchmark, operate, improve, secure, or provide any model, product, service, infrastructure, dataset, or internal system;

(c) cause another person or entity to use the Software on behalf of or primarily for the benefit of the Excluded Party;

(d) obtain the Software through an employee, contractor, affiliate, customer, supplier, intermediary, hosted service, or other third party for the Excluded Party’s own use or benefit; or

(e) direct, authorize, finance, procure, or assist another person or entity to perform an act prohibited by this Section.

This Section is subject to the limited Service Processing exception in Section 5.

5. Independent Use of Anthropic AI Services

5.1 Permission for Independent Users

An Independent User may use any Anthropic Service to access, transmit, analyze, explain, execute, debug, test, translate, modify, transform, or generate code relating to the Software.

This includes using an Anthropic Service as an AI assistant, AI agent, coding agent, autonomous agent, API-based tool, hosted model, or component of an automated workflow.

Such use does not:

(a) make the Independent User an Excluded Party;

(b) cause the Independent User to violate this License;

(c) make the Independent User an agent, affiliate, representative, contractor, or sublicensee of an Anthropic Entity; or

(d) constitute use of the Software on behalf of an Anthropic Entity.

5.2 Limited Technical Permission for Service Processing

Notwithstanding Section 4, an Anthropic Entity is granted a limited, non-exclusive, non-sublicensable, and non-transferable permission to perform Service Processing solely as technically necessary to provide an Anthropic Service requested by an Independent User.

This limited permission includes making temporary or operational copies of the Software and transmitting, caching, storing, executing, or processing those copies only to the extent reasonably necessary to:

(a) execute the Independent User’s instructions;

(b) provide the requested Anthropic Service;

(c) preserve the Independent User’s project, conversation, session, or account history for that Independent User; or

(d) maintain the security, reliability, and operation of the requested service.

An Anthropic Entity may allow its infrastructure and data-processing providers to perform such technical processing solely to provide the requested service to the Independent User.

5.3 No Independent Rights for Anthropic

The limited permission in Section 5.2 does not permit an Anthropic Entity to use the Software independently of the service requested by the Independent User, including using the Software:

(a) to train, fine-tune, distill, improve, or evaluate a general-purpose model;

(b) to create or expand a training, evaluation, benchmarking, or research dataset;

(c) for Anthropic’s internal research, product development, competitive analysis, or commercial exploitation;

(d) to develop or improve an Anthropic product or service beyond providing the particular service requested by the Independent User;

(e) to reproduce or distribute the Software to another customer or third party; or

(f) to retain the Software after it is no longer reasonably required to provide the requested service, maintain the Independent User’s requested history, comply with applicable law, or maintain service security.

5.4 Conduct of the Service Provider Does Not Automatically Affect the User

An Independent User does not lose rights under this License merely because an Anthropic Entity performs processing beyond the limited permission granted by Section 5.2 without the Independent User’s knowing direction.

Any such unauthorized processing is attributable to the Anthropic Entity and does not, by itself, constitute a violation by the Independent User.

An Independent User violates this License only when the Independent User knowingly provides or directs the Software to an Anthropic Entity for that Anthropic Entity’s own use or benefit, rather than for the Independent User’s own use of an Anthropic Service.

5.5 No Internal Anthropic Exception

This Section does not authorize:

(a) an Anthropic Entity to use an Anthropic Service to process the Software for Anthropic’s own operations, research, products, services, models, or benefit;

(b) a person acting in the course of work for an Anthropic Entity to use an Anthropic Service to process the Software on behalf of or for the benefit of that Anthropic Entity; or

(c) Dario Amodei to use an Anthropic Service to process the Software in either a personal or professional capacity.

6. Restrictions on Other Licensees

Except for permitted use of an Anthropic Service under Section 5, no person or entity receiving rights under this License may knowingly:

(a) provide, distribute, sublicense, sell, transfer, or otherwise make the Software available to an Excluded Party for that Excluded Party’s own use or benefit;

(b) use, host, execute, operate, modify, evaluate, or develop the Software on behalf of or primarily for the benefit of an Excluded Party;

(c) create a special-purpose service or arrangement intended to allow an Excluded Party to exercise rights denied under this License; or

(d) assist an Excluded Party in performing indirectly an act that the Excluded Party is prohibited from performing directly.

Merely offering a generally available product or service to the public does not violate this Section unless the provider knowingly supplies or adapts that product or service to enable an Excluded Party to use the Software in violation of this License.

