8. Termination

Rights granted under this License to a person or entity terminate automatically and immediately when that person or entity violates this License.

Upon termination, the violating person or entity must immediately:

(a) cease all unauthorized use, access, modification, hosting, operation, and distribution of the Software;

(b) delete or destroy all unauthorized copies of the Software within its possession or control; and

(c) cease providing any product or service whose operation constitutes a continuing violation of this License.

Rights terminated under this Section may be restored only through express written permission from the copyright holder.

Termination applies only to the violating person or entity and does not affect rights validly exercised by compliant Independent Users.

